{{Infobox glacier | child = | name = Beaver Glacier (Ross Ice Shelf) | other_name = | photo = | photo_width = | photo_alt = | photo_caption = | map = Antarctica | map_width = | map_alt = | map_caption = Location of Beaver Glacier (Ross Ice Shelf) in [[Antarctica]] | mark = Blue_pog.svg | type = | location = [[Ross Dependency]] | coordinates = {{coord|83|24|S|169|30|E|region:AQ|format=dms|display=inline}} | coords_ref = | area = | length = {{convert|24|km|mi|abbr=on}} | width = | thickness = unknown | elevation_max = | elevation_min = | terminus = [[Ross Ice Shelf]] | status = unknown | embedded = }}
'''Beaver Glacier''' ({{coord|83|24|S|169|30|E|type:glacier_region:AQ_source:GNIS|display=inline,title}}) is a [[glacier]], {{convert|15|mi}} long, draining the coastal mountains of the [[Queen Alexandra Range]] just northwest of [[Mount Fox (Antarctica)|Mount Fox]] and entering the [[Ross Ice Shelf]] at [[McCann Point]]. It was named by the [[New Zealand Geological Survey Antarctic Expedition]] (1959–60) after the [[De Havilland Canada DHC-2 Beaver|Beaver aircraft]] ''City of Auckland'', which crashed in this area in January 1960.
