'''Bornmann Glacier''' ({{Coord|72|20|S|170|13|E|source:GNIS|display=inline,title}}) is a [[glacier]] flowing from the west side of [[Hallett Peninsula]] {{convert|1|nmi|km|0}} south of [[Seabee Hook]] and forming a short, floating ice tongue on the shore of [[Edisto Inlet]]. It was named by the [[New Zealand Geological Survey Antarctic Expedition]], 1957–58, for Lieutenant [[Robert C. Bornmann]], MC, [[U.S. Navy]], surgeon and leader of the U.S. Navy [[Operation Deep Freeze]] party at [[Hallett Station]] in 1958.<ref name=gnis/>

