'''Carl Julius Bernhard Börner''' (28 May 1880 &ndash; 14 June 1953) was a [[Germany|German]] [[entomologist]].

Börner was born in [[Bremen]] and died in [[Naumburg]]. His collections of [[Collembola]] are located in the [[Natural History Museum, London|Natural History Museum]], [[London]] and the [[Deutsches Entomologisches Institut]] in [[Müncheberg]].

