An '''E-micro''' is a [[futures contract]] traded on the [[Chicago Mercantile Exchange]]'s [[Globex]] [[electronic trading platform]], that represent an even smaller fraction of the value of the normal futures contracts, than the corresponding [[E-mini]].
Currently, CME offers one E-micro [[stock market index]] contract, ''E-micro S&P CNX Nifty (Nifty 50) Futures'', with a [[notional value]] of $2 x the [[S&P CNX Nifty]] index of Indian stocks,<ref>{{cite web|title=E-micro S&P CNX Nifty (Nifty 50) futures - Contract specifications|url=http://www.cmegroup.com/trading/equity-index/international-index/emicro-sandp-cnx-nifty-50-futures_contract_specifications.html|publisher=[[Chicago Mercantile Exchange|CME]] Group|accessdate=16 April 2011}}</ref> and E-micro contracts for a number of [[currency futures]] pegged against the US Dollar (AUD, CAD, CHF, EUR, GBP, JPY).<ref>{{cite web|title=CME ClearPort Product Slate - FX E-micros|url=http://www.cmegroup.com/trading/otc/index.html#FilterOn=//lcpcProductTO%5Bcpcproduct/product_group%20+%20'FX'%20and%20cpcproduct/sub_group%20+%20'E%20Micros'%5D|publisher=CME Group|accessdate=16 April 2011}}</ref> E-micro [[gold]] futures contracts were introduced in October 2010.<ref>{{cite web|title=Introducing The New E-Micro Gold Futures -- Making Prices Even Easier To Manipulate|url=http://www.businessinsider.com/new-micro-gold-futures-will-make-market-manipulation-acessible-to-the-little-guy-2010-10|publisher=Business Insider, Inc|first=Vincent|last=Fernando|date=6 October 2010|accessdate=16 April 2011}}</ref>
