== A == * [[Wilhelm Altekruse]], inventor of [[Altekruse Puzzle]] [[Image:Auer von Welsbach.jpg|thumb|right|150px|[[Carl Auer von Welsbach]].]] * [[Carl Auer von Welsbach]], work on [[rare-earth element]]s, which led to the development of the [[ferrocerium|flint]] used in modern [[lighter]]s, the [[gas mantle]] which brought light to the streets of Europe in the late 19th century, and the development of the metal filament [[light bulb]].
== B == [[Image:Georg Joseph Beer.jpg|thumb|right|150px|[[Georg Joseph Beer]].]] * [[Georg Joseph Beer]], introducing a flap operation for treatment of [[cataract]]s ([[Beer's operation]]), as well as popularizing the instrument used to perform the surgery (Beer's knife). * [[Günther Burstyn]], co-inventor of the [[tank]] (independent from him [[William Tritton]] and [[Walter Gordon Wilson]]) <!-- http://www.bmlv.gv.at/truppendienst/ausgaben/artikel.php?id=869 -->
== C == * [[Carl Cori]] (nobel prize), co-discovered [[Cori cycle]]. * [[Gerty Cori]] (nobel prize), co-discovered Cori cycle.
== D == * [[Carl Djerassi]], inventor of [[birth control pills]] * [[Christian Doppler]], discoverer of the [[Doppler effect]]
== E == * [[Paul Eisler]], inventor of the [[printed circuit board]].
== F == [[Image:Sigmund Freud, by Max Halberstadt (cropped).jpg|thumb|right|150px|Sigmund Freud]] *[[Otto Frenzl]]: Aeronautical pioneer, developed the [[area rule]] in 1943, a design technique for airfoils used to reduce an aircraft's drag at transonic and supersonic speeds. Later it was independently developed again by [[Richard T. Whitcomb]] in 1952. * [[Sigmund Freud]]: [[Neurologist]] who became known as the founding father of [[psychoanalysis]] * [[Karl von Frisch]] (nobel prize), one of the founders of modern [[ethology]], studies on [[waggle dance]] * [[Paul Fürst]], inventor of the [[Mozartkugel]]
== G == * [[David Gestetner]], inventor of the [[Gestetner]] [[stencil duplicator]]. * [[Adolph Giesl-Gieslingen]], inventor of the [[Giesl ejector]]
== H == * [[Friedrich Hayek]] (nobel prize), pioneering work in the [[monetary policy|theory of money]] and [[Business cycle|economic fluctuations]]. [[Image:Hess.jpg|right|150px|thumb|[[Victor Francis Hess]].]] * [[Victor Francis Hess]] (nobel prize), discovered [[cosmic ray]]. * [[Ingeborg Hochmair]], developed the first modern [[cochlear implant]]
